h^n
\frac d{dx} \exp\left\{\frac x2\left(h-\frac1h\right) \right\} =\frac 12\left(h-\frac1h\right) \sum_{-\infty}^\infty h^n J_n(x)=\frac 12 \left(\sum_{-\infty}^\infty h^{n} J_{n-1}(x) - \sum_{-\infty}^\infty h^{n} J_{n+1}(x)\right)\\\frac d{dx}\sum_{-\infty}^\infty h^n J_n(x)=\sum_{-\infty}^\infty h^n\frac d{dx} J_n(x)
